text: Warren Rino (born 3 September 1993) is a French Guianan footballer who currently plays for AJ Saint-Georges in the French Guiana Honor Division and the French Guiana national team. == International career == Rino made his national team debut for French Guiana on 8 June 2018 in a 2–0 win against Guadeloupe. Rino scored his first goal and first competitive goal on 7 September 2018, scoring the opening goal in a 5–0 win against Anguilla, as part of 2019–20 CONCACAF Nations League qualifying. === International goals === :Scores and results list French Guiana's goal tally first. {| class="wikitable" style="font-size:95%" |- ! # !!
